  "title": "ACMV Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform <strong>preventive maintenance </strong>on air conditioning systems (split units, VRF/VRV, central systems).</li><li>Conduct routine inspections cleaning, and servicing of filters, coils, and condensers.</li><li>Diagnose and repair mechanical, electrical, and refrigerant-related faults.</li><li>Replace defective components such as compressors, motors, and sensors.</li><li>Monitor system performance and maintain accurate service records.</li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>safety, environmental, and regulatory standards</strong>.</li><li>Provide technical advice and updates to clients regarding system condition.</li><li>Collaborate with facilities managers and train junior technicians when required.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering, or HVAC specialization.</li><li>5 years of experience in <strong>air conditioning maintenance</strong>.</li><li>Strong knowledge of HVAC systems, refrigerants, and electrical controls.</li><li>Certification in refrigerant handling (EPA or local equivalent) preferred.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Excellent troubleshooting and repair skills.</li><li>Strong problem-solving and time management abilities.</li><li>Good communication and customer service skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</li></ul><p>Interested applicants may submit their CVs to <a href=\"https://employer.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/jobs/green-mark-manager-stie-769581bb59bdc506520729b577dd5381/view\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">skh_hr@stie.com.sg</a> or apply directly via the “Apply”\nbutton on CareersFuture.</p>",
